Ohanaeze Ndigbo has said that the planned visit of President Muhammadu Buhari to Ebonyi State this week will open another opportunity for agreement on the release of the Leader of the proscribed Indigenous People of Biafra (IPOB), Mazi Nnamdi Kanu. According to a press release issued by Mazi Okechukwu Isiguzoro, Secretary-General of Ohanaeze Ndigbo, the Elders council of the group had in a meeting presided over by Dr Richard Ozobu noted that the two-day working visit of Buhari is the best opportunity for Igbo leaders with the southeast Governors to dialogue with the President over the release of Kanu. “Ndigbo expectations are that such windows of opportunities must be fully utilized for positive results as President Buhari will be received warmly by Ndigbo, this will be one of the most remarkable visits of Mr President to the southeast, as we except that the President’s two days working visit to Ebonyi state will change the narratives that Buhari loves Ndigbo, and he will prove it by kick-starting the process that will release Nnamdi Kanu”. -Advertisement- The document made available to Daily Independent in Abakaliki explained that Ipob and other Biafra agitators should hold their peace and remain loyal to the procedure that will help them achieve the release of their leader, Mazi Nnamdi Kanu. “Buhari’s visit will usher in fresh hopes of having a Nigerian President of Igbo Extraction and secure the release of Mazi Nnamdi Kanu, we are conscious of the fact that Ipob is cognizant of the process of releasing their leader is ongoing, and their proper attitudes and conducts are expected to solidify the process of Kanu’s release, we are welcoming President Buhari with an open mind and wish him a pleasant stay in Ebonyi State”. They gave assurances of peace and security ahead of the planned presidential visit to the state. “This is part of the resolutions reached at the Ohanaeze Ndigbo Elders council meeting held in Abakiliki on Tuesday 3rd May 2022, for translucence and clarity of purpose, President Mohammadu Buhari has been fair to Ndigbo with Federal Projects irrespective of the fact that his party’s declined fortunes and acceptance in 2015 and 2019 elections in the southeast” “The Chairman of Southeast Governors and Ebonyi Governor, Engr Dave Nweze Umahi has brought good tidings and paid huge sacrifices for Ndigbo to access the presidency and attract federal government’s projects and attention to the southeast zone”.